{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Provide a grant equal to November 2019 revenues for businesses required to close",
        "additional_details": "Sectors forced to close during the spring lockdown invested significantly to open when allowed to open earlier this year and to prepare for winter. The lockdown announced for November 2020 will be devastating for these businesses, and the furlough scheme will not go far enough to help. The measures announced on 31 October gave no time for businesses to adapt and prepare and will be devastating without significant support.",
        "background": "All businesses required to close during the second lockdown in November 2020 should be provided with a grant equal to their revenues in November 2019, or 1/12th of their 2019 revenues.",
